What are semantic tags in HTML?

Answer:
Semantic tags are HTML tags that clearly describe the purpose of the content they contain. Examples include <header>, <nav>, <section>, <article>, <aside>, <main>, and <footer>. They improve readability, accessibility, and SEO.

